"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM posts\nJOIN users ON posts.OwnerUserId = users.Id\nWHERE users.Age > 65 AND posts.Score >= 20;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of posts that are owned by users classified as \"elder\" (age greater than 65) and have a score of 20 or more. The query joins the `posts` table with the `users` table using the `OwnerUserId` foreign key to match posts with their respective owners."